title: Test
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 6 lines representing Paraffinic Group I, Paraffinic Group II, Paraffinic Group III, Naphthenic, Synthetic, and Other.
The line for Paraffinic Group I has the highest values across Year with a mean value of 45.67,
and it peaked at 2015 with a value of 54.0.
Followed by Paraffinic Group II, with a mean value of 26.0.
This line peaked at 2030 with a value of 31.0.
Other mostly had the least y-axis name with a mean value of 1.0,
which peaked at 2020 with a value of 2.0.
Other reported the lowest y-axis name  about 0.0 in Year 2030
Overall Paraffinic Group II, and Paraffinic Group III are gradually increasing, Paraffinic Group I is gradually decreasing, Naphthenic, Synthetic, and Other are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
